dismissalText.commentary: Ben Stokes obstructing the field 10 (7b 1x4 0x6 18m) SR: 142.85

dismissalComment.html: pretty full and on the stumps at 145ks, Stokes drives back to the bowler, who stretches his left hand and plucks it out. He has a aim at the stumps (sensing a run-out chance), Stokes, who is out of the crease, fends the throw off with his left glove/ instinctively looks to protect himself, as he loses his balance and collapses on the floor. Wade goes up. Starc appeals. Umpires Dharmasena and Robinson converge. The soft signal is not out. Stokes has been given out obstructing the field by the TV umpire Joe Wilson. Smith, Morgan intervene and have a chat with the umpires. Boos ring around Lord's. Morgan isn't happy. Stokes drags himself off the field. Roy, in the balcony, can't believe it. Drama! Drama!

dismissalText.commentary: Eoin Morgan c Maxwell b Cummins 85 (87b 4x4 4x6 135m) SR: 97.7

commentTextItems.html: gone this time, that's the end of an amazing innings by Morgan and a really, good match. Australia win by 64 runs. Morgan and Smith have a chat while shaking hands. Good length outside off, Morgan looks to clear the long-off boundary with a heave but the ball lobs up nicely and sits in long-off's lap. Australia go 2-0 up in the five-match series.

commentPostTextItems.html: 7.00pm Steven Smith was booed off the field after his presentation. Lots of interpretations regarding the Stokes' dismissal. Sets up interestingly for the third ODI on Tuesday. Till then, ciao.
6.50pm England are currently having a closed-doors meeting. Hence, the presentation has been slightly delayed.

Eoin Morgan: "After winning the toss and bowling, it was important to hold our disciplines but we failed to do so. We are a learning team and playing against a tough opposition who are a well-drilled side. Managed to get some time in the middle an you get good value for runs here at the Home of cricket. It's difficult, when a guy throws a ball at you from 5 yards its difficult to get out of the way, it was what it was. The decision was given. Yep (when asked if he would have withdrawn the appeal).

Steven Smith: "It's disappointing, the decision was given and the umpires saw it the way we saw it. That was the decision made, I don't want to shy away from the face we played some good cricket. I thought our fielding was quite sloppy. Still lots of improvement to be done in the remaining games."

Mitchell Marsh is the Man of the Match. "It's been a nice start. Hopefully, this can continue. We have all worked extremely hard. It's a great all-round win. Was swinging a bit too hard (in the previous game).

6.35pm Righto, lots of talking points today. Firstly, it has been an entertaining match. England, like in the first ODI, were on course for good chunks of the chase but lost wickets too frequently to really stand a chance. Lots of starts but a point worth mentioning was Eoin Morgan's fighting innings, a really brisk, clever 85.

Among those wickets, was the dismissal of Ben Stokes who was given out obstructing the field. Was he taking evasive action? Did the left hand come out too far as he blocked the ball from hitting the stumps? The third umpire looked at replays and gave him out, which from his point of view and according to me, was the right call. That wicket certainly pushed England back and didn't find their way back till Morgan's late blitz. Another important factor is David Warner is out of the series with a fractured thumb.

Srihari: "Amidst all the hoopla surrounding the Stokes dismissal, what must not be forgotten is the real reason why England are 0-2 down in the series. Their top order's failure to convert starts into big scores is what cost them both games."

commentTextItems.html: oh, they steal the single. Good length but closer to off, Finn is hit on the thighs and Morgan calls him through for the single as the ball rolls towards point. There is a quick but inaccurate throw at the non-strikers end.
good length outside off, Finn chooses to leave the ball
they manage to stop the single as well. Very quick low full toss, Morgan looks to heave but skews the ball to short cover who is tight on the one. Good captaincy
another well-executed yorker, speared in with some reverse on off, Morgan drives to mid-off

commentPreTextItems.html: Rajitha: "Plunkett gave it up. Should've calmed down for a couple of balls or so..."

commentTextItems.html: full yorker outside off, Morgan cannot get under that, he drives to cover and refuses the single
full and overpitched on leg, Finn does his job as he nurdles behind square for one
wide from Starc. Goes for the bouncer but drifts down leg.

commentPreTextItems.html: Haz: "With hindsight, just how crucial was that Stokes wicket? Just two wickets left in this situation makes England's position far more precarious than having 4 or 5."

commentTextItems.html: quick yorker attempted but ends up as a low full toss. Finn manages to keep it out.

commentPostTextItems.html: Keep the bat down would be my suggestion to Finn

commentPreTextItems.html: Mitchell Starc returns. Boos ring around Lord's. Lots of optimism in the crowd though.

and another with not as much timing though. Very full and wide, Morgan skews the ball over cover for two.

headshotImage.caption: Liam Plunkett player page headshot cutout, 2021
headshotImage.longCaption: Liam Plunkett player page headshot cutout, 2021

commentTextItems.html: Morgan is at it again. What a shot. Absolutely stunning to watch. He gives himself some room and smashes the ball over cover for another boundary. Hmm, gettin' interestin'.
just the one this time. Very full outside off, Plunkett lofts the ball with no timing over cover

commentPreTextItems.html: george: "Give billings another chance this series"

commentTextItems.html: edged for four this time. Luck certainly favouring the brave Plunkett who advances and looks to force through the off side.
nice delivery, yorker on off stump, Morgan can only drill the ball to long-off
slower offcutter outside off, Morgan shuffles across but hits the man at point.
just falls short. Plunkett drives the fullish length to mid-off. Smashed that. Lord's is bustling once again.

commentPostTextItems.html: DuncanR: "Both teams scored 19 off the 39th over to be dead even at 213 after 39; just 5 wickets separating them"

headshotImage.longCaption: Liam Plunkett player page headshot cutout, 2021

commentTextItems.html: fourth boundary of the over. Just a hint too short from Cummins who swipes the ball through midwicket for another four runs.
and another one. WOW. Short and wide, definitely a poor delivery by Cummins. Plunkett gets behind the line and plays a really nice cut through point. Well timed too.
down leg this time. Cummins was looking to follow Plunkett who backed away, strays too wide though

dismissalComment.html: The middle stump is tiled back. Finn shoots through Burns' gate. He has been pretty good with the drive but fails this time. This was full and curves in, Burns sets up for a drive and does not connect. Finn rips through the bat-pad gap and that's timbaaaah!

dismissalText.commentary: George Bailey b Ali 54 (72b 5x4 0x6 78m) SR: 75

dismissalComment.html: and the change works. Maybe a loss in concentration by Bailey but that turned a mile. Beautiful drift by Moeen. Tossed up outside off with plenty of drift, pitches outside off and spins in to beat Bailey's flaying bat and take leg stump. Not only an offspinner's dream ball but a very vital wicket too.

headshotImage.caption: Adil Rashid player page headshot cutout, 2021
headshotImage.longCaption: Adil Rashid player page headshot cutout, 2021

dismissalText.commentary: Steven Smith c Taylor b Rashid 70 (87b 7x4 0x6 133m) SR: 80.45

dismissalComment.html: oh, he's gone this time. Tame dismissal for Smith. He is distraught, nothing wicket for Rashid. Tossed up nicely outside off and Smith looks to drive through cover but the ball skews to point off the outer half of the bat

dismissalText.commentary: Glenn Maxwell lbw b Finn 49 (38b 4x4 3x6 41m) SR: 128.94

dismissalComment.html: No fifty for Maxwell. Umpire Dharmasena's finger goes up. Maxwell has a chat with Watson and decides not to review. Nice and full and on middle, Maxwell shuffles across and topples over the flick as he is rapped on the front pad. Trapped in front..

headshotImage.longCaption: Ben Stokes player page headshot cutout, 2021

headshotImage.caption: Liam Plunkett player page headshot cutout, 2021
headshotImage.longCaption: Liam Plunkett player page headshot cutout, 2021

dismissalText.commentary: Shane Watson c Plunkett b Stokes 39 (38b 1x4 2x6 55m) SR: 102.63

dismissalComment.html: Watson missed a kick in the T20I, he was a victim of a poor call and was run-out in the first ODI, he has holed off a low full toss in this game. Watson did not get under this properly and hit it straight down the throat of long-on. Stokes fires in a wicked stare...

headshotImage.longCaption: Ben Stokes player page headshot cutout, 2021

headshotImage.caption: Ben Stokes player page headshot cutout, 2021
headshotImage.longCaption: Ben Stokes player page headshot cutout, 2021

dismissalText.commentary: Matthew Wade c & b Stokes 1 (2b 0x4 0x6 6m) SR: 50

dismissalComment.html: short, lifting ball outside off. Wade is hurried onto a pull, he skews it in the air off a top edge, which is swallowed by Stokes himself. Simple return catch. The batsmen cross over and Marsh will be on strike

headshotImage.caption: Ben Stokes player page headshot cutout, 2021
headshotImage.longCaption: Ben Stokes player page headshot cutout, 2021

dismissalText.commentary: Mitchell Marsh c Buttler b Stokes 64 (31b 7x4 3x6 43m) SR: 206.45

dismissalComment.html: Marsh pops it behind off the last ball of the innings. Short, slower ball down the leg side at 110.4ks. Marsh was far too early into the pull and could only glove it to Buttler. Marsh has done his job, though, muscling Australia past 300

headshotImage.caption: Jason Roy player page headshot cutout, 2021
headshotImage.longCaption: Jason Roy player page headshot cutout, 2021

headshotImage.caption: Jason Roy player page headshot cutout, 2021
headshotImage.longCaption: Jason Roy player page headshot cutout, 2021

dismissalText.commentary: Jason Roy c Wade b Cummins 31 (32b 6x4 0x6 53m) SR: 96.87

dismissalComment.html: gone this time. Roy has thrown another one away. Very poor shot considering the circumstances. Full outside off, cross-seam, maybe generating some extra bounce. Roy, however, loosely wafts at the ball and gets a thick outside edge. Wade takes a good diving catch to his right.

dismissalText.commentary: Alex Hales c Smith b Coulter-Nile 18 (20b 4x4 0x6 25m) SR: 90

dismissalComment.html: what a catch. Stunning stuff from Smith. Absolutely stunning. Fuller length outside off, Hales skews the drive off the outer half of the bat towards short cover where Smith is lurking, he dives high to his right to take a spectacular, two-handed catch.

dismissalText.commentary: James Taylor c Wade b Marsh 43 (57b 5x4 0x6 68m) SR: 75.43

dismissalComment.html: Taylor nicks behind. Good length and largely holds its line outside off, Taylor seeks to run it fine to third man. But can only outside-edge it to Wade. Marsh takes high-fives from his team-mates

dismissalText.commentary: Eoin Morgan c Maxwell b Cummins 85 (87b 4x4 4x6 135m) SR: 97.7

dismissalComment.html: gone this time, that's the end of an amazing innings by Morgan and a really, good match. Australia win by 64 runs. Morgan and Smith have a chat while shaking hands. Good length outside off, Morgan looks to clear the long-off boundary with a heave but the ball lobs up nicely and sits in long-off's lap. Australia go 2-0 up in the five-match series.

headshotImage.caption: Ben Stokes player page headshot cutout, 2021
headshotImage.longCaption: Ben Stokes player page headshot cutout, 2021

headshotImage.caption: Ben Stokes player page headshot cutout, 2021
headshotImage.longCaption: Ben Stokes player page headshot cutout, 2021

dismissalText.commentary: Ben Stokes obstructing the field 10 (7b 1x4 0x6 18m) SR: 142.85

dismissalComment.html: pretty full and on the stumps at 145ks, Stokes drives back to the bowler, who stretches his left hand and plucks it out. He has a aim at the stumps (sensing a run-out chance), Stokes, who is out of the crease, fends the throw off with his left glove/ instinctively looks to protect himself, as he loses his balance and collapses on the floor. Wade goes up. Starc appeals. Umpires Dharmasena and Robinson converge. The soft signal is not out. Stokes has been given out obstructing the field by the TV umpire Joe Wilson. Smith, Morgan intervene and have a chat with the umpires. Boos ring around Lord's. Morgan isn't happy. Stokes drags himself off the field. Roy, in the balcony, can't believe it. Drama! Drama!

dismissalText.commentary: Jos Buttler lbw b Maxwell 0 (3b 0x4 0x6 5m) SR: 0

dismissalComment.html: an appeal for lbw, Tim Robinson does not budge. Australia want a review. Maxi's front foot is fine. Flighted on middle, with a hint of turn. He misses the defensive push, is beaten on the inside edge and is rapped on the front pad. The ball pitched in line, impact in line, it would have hit the top of middle. Buttler is sent packing for a three-ball duck..

dismissalText.commentary: Moeen Ali c Marsh b Maxwell 8 (15b 0x4 0x6 19m) SR: 53.33

dismissalComment.html: gone this time. Moeen goes. Another rather soft wicket. Moeen gets down to sweep and gets a thick top edge, the ball flies off towards deep square leg who settles under it early and takes an easy catch. Nothing delivery from Maxwell but England in serious trouble now.

dismissalText.commentary: Chris Woakes c Wade b Cummins 6 (12b 1x4 0x6 11m) SR: 50

dismissalComment.html: is that out? Given. Woakes goes now. England falling apart. Woakes looks to swivel-pull the ball into the leg side but gets a thick inside edge which carries low to Wade. Lord's is quiet. The Stokes dismissal has had a bearing impact on the game.

dismissalText.commentary: Adil Rashid c Coulter-Nile b Cummins 2 (8b 0x4 0x6 10m) SR: 25

dismissalComment.html: another wicket. If England were in trouble then, they are in deeper trouble now. Fullish on off, Rashid clips the ball uppishly and straight to mid-on, where NCN takes a diving catch to his left.
